      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nausea and tremors are common side effects when starting lithium, so it's important to monitor them closely. However, since you're concerned, you should definitely discuss these symptoms with your prescribing physician right away. Regarding hydration, drinking more water is excellent advice, as dehydration can worsen some side effects and is crucial when taking lithium. Do not ignore the water intake; aim to be consistently well-hydrated.",
